==English==

===Etymology===
Japanese [[都]] ([[みやこ]], miyako) “capital” (as the city was formerly the capital of Japan).

===Proper noun===
'''Meaco'''
# A late medieval name for [[Kyoto]], a city of Japan.
# (by extension) The entire island of [[Honshu]] which it was capital of. 

